comment:
* Column definitions for the TV programs that the user watched. Applications do not have access * to this table. * *

By default, the query results will be sorted by * {@link WatchedPrograms#COLUMN_WATCH_START_TIME_UTC_MILLIS} in descending order. * @hide

variables.name: CONTENT_URI
variables.comment: The content:// style URI for this table.

variables.name: CONTENT_TYPE
variables.comment: The MIME type of a directory of watched programs.

variables.name: CONTENT_ITEM_TYPE
variables.comment: The MIME type of a single item in this table.

variables.name: COLUMN_WATCH_START_TIME_UTC_MILLIS
variables.comment:
* The UTC time that the user started watching this TV program, in milliseconds since the * epoch. * *

Type: INTEGER (long)

variables.name: COLUMN_WATCH_END_TIME_UTC_MILLIS
variables.comment:
* The UTC time that the user stopped watching this TV program, in milliseconds since the * epoch. * *

Type: INTEGER (long)

variables.name: COLUMN_CHANNEL_ID
variables.comment:
* The ID of the TV channel that provides this TV program. * *

This is a required field. * *

Type: INTEGER (long)

variables.name: COLUMN_TITLE
variables.comment:
* The title of this TV program. * *

Type: TEXT

variables.name: COLUMN_START_TIME_UTC_MILLIS
variables.comment:
* The start time of this TV program, in milliseconds since the epoch. * *

Type: INTEGER (long)

variables.name: COLUMN_END_TIME_UTC_MILLIS
variables.comment:
* The end time of this TV program, in milliseconds since the epoch. * *

Type: INTEGER (long)

variables.name: COLUMN_DESCRIPTION
variables.comment:
* The description of this TV program. * *

Type: TEXT

variables.name: COLUMN_INTERNAL_TUNE_PARAMS
variables.comment:
* Extra parameters given to {@link TvInputService.Session#tune(Uri, android.os.Bundle) * TvInputService.Session.tune(Uri, android.os.Bundle)} when tuning to the channel that * provides this TV program. (Used internally.) * *

This column contains an encoded string that represents comma-separated key-value pairs of * the tune parameters. (Ex. "[key1]=[value1], [key2]=[value2]"). '%' is used as an escape * character for '%', '=', and ','. * *

Type: TEXT

variables.name: COLUMN_INTERNAL_SESSION_TOKEN
variables.comment:
* The session token of this TV program. (Used internally.) * *

This contains a String representation of {@link IBinder} for * {@link TvInputService.Session} that provides the current TV program. It is used * internally to distinguish watched programs entries from different TV input sessions. * *

Type: TEXT
